
You can also create default nibbles.conf configuration file there, where you specify ports to listen, default print filters, UDP log file and so on.

At runtime you can toggle different windows by pressing F2, F3, F4, F5 and F6.




Nibbles supports loading/saving ethernet messages 
'''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''

to/from a msgtemplate file. You can save message you specify at runtime and it will be stored to .nibbles folder in your home directory and is loaded at next startup.




Nibbles 1.0-2 supports simplified C define/struct lookup. 
'''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''

In order to enable it, please:

create .nibbles folder in your home directory.
create Interface folder ~/.nibbles and place C headers with definitions in that folder. (Usable when you have structs for messages to be sent over ethernet).

or run ./install.sh and answer to all the questions.

--Enjoy.
